description:
This week Kate talks the 12th anniversary of her mom’s death, the ways in which grief is constantly changing, and her progress with therapy and intuitive eating. Doree details her luxurious bath routine whilst in New York, visiting family, and how she’s staying hydrated while pregnant.

Then they welcome actor and writer Natasha Rothwell (HBO’s Insecure). She breaks down why she recently embraced meditation, astrology and self-help books, how getting a dog transformed her life, and shares tips for handling imposter syndrome.
